  <recipe>
    <head>
      <title>Wafer Wrapped Prawns</title>
      <categories>
        <cat>Fondue</cat>
        <cat>Seafood</cat></categories>
      <yield>4</yield></head>
    <ingredients>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>12</qty>
          <unit>ounces</unit></amt>
        <item>Prawns -- peeled &amp; chopped</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit/></amt>
        <item>Green chile -- seeded and</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty/>
          <unit/></amt>
        <item>Chopped</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>2</qty>
          <unit>teaspoons</unit></amt>
        <item>Oyster sauce</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>2</qty>
          <unit/></amt>
        <item>Sheets filo pastry</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty/>
          <unit/></amt>
        <item>SAUCE</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>4</qty>
          <unit>tablespoons</unit></amt>
        <item>Tomato sauce</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit>teaspoon</unit></amt>
        <item>Chilli sauce</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1/2</qty>
          <unit>teaspoons</unit></amt>
        <item>Sesame oil</item></ing></ingredients>
    <directions>
      <step>  In a bowl mix together prawns, chilli and oyster sauce.
  
  Cut filo pastry into 4 inch squares. Place a heaped teaspoon of prawn
  filling in the centre of each square, draw the corners of the pastry
  together and twist to form little bundles. Place on a floured serving plate
  and chill until required.
  
  To make sauce, pour tomato sauce, chilli sauce, 2 tablespoons water and
  sesame oil into a saucepan and heat gently for 3-4 minutes. serve hot with
  the prawn bundles cooked in hot oil.
  
